      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Salt and fry the aubergine",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sprinkle {{aubergine}} slices of aubergine with {{sea-salt-fine}} of salt and leave on a tray for 20 minutes. Pat dry with kitchen paper. Heat the {{olive-oil}} of olive oil in batches in a large frying pan over medium-high heat; fry the aubergine slices for 2 minutes per side until golden. Drain on kitchen paper and set aside.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the meat sauce",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the same pan, cook {{onion}} diced onion in a little oil for 8 minutes until soft. Add {{garlic}} of chopped garlic for 2 minutes. Add {{lamb-mince}} of lamb mince and brown for 8 minutes, breaking it up. Add {{red-wine}} of red wine; let it reduce for 3 minutes. Add {{tinned-tomatoes}} of tinned tomatoes, {{tomato-puree}} of tomato purée, {{cinnamon-ground}} of cinnamon and {{allspice}} of allspice. Simmer for 20 minutes until very thick, almost dry.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the béchamel",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt {{unsalted-butter}} of butter in a saucepan. Add {{plain-flour}} of flour; stir for 2 minutes. Gradually whisk in {{whole-milk}} of milk until smooth. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring, until thick enough to coat the back of a spoon. Remove from the heat. Stir in {{parmesan}} of Parmesan and {{nutmeg-ground}} of nutmeg. Cool for 5 minutes then beat in {{eggs}} eggs.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C. Layer half the aubergine in a deep baking dish. Spread all the meat sauce evenly over. Layer the remaining aubergine on top. Pour the béchamel over the surface in an even layer. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until the top is set and deep golden. Leave to rest for 20 minutes before cutting; moussaka must rest or it will collapse when served.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Troubleshooting",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": null,
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Rest for a full 20 minutes. The béchamel must be very thick before it goes on top; add the eggs only after it cools slightly.",
              "cause": "Not rested long enough, or béchamel not thick enough.",
              "symptom": "Layers collapsing when cut"
            },
            {
              "fix": "The meat sauce must simmer until almost dry before layering. Any liquid will leach into the aubergine and make the dish wet.",
              "cause": "Meat sauce not reduced enough.",
              "symptom": "Watery meat layer"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Use a wide, shallow dish for better browning. Switch to the grill for the last 5 minutes if the top needs more colour.",
              "cause": "Oven not hot enough, or dish too deep.",
              "symptom": "Pale, soft béchamel top"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "Common problems"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Moussaka in Greece is Sunday cooking: something made in a large dish in the morning, left to cool, cut and served at a table with many people around it. It travels well to the next day, when the flavours have settled and each layer has firmed. It is a dish for a gathering, not an impromptu Thursday dinner, and it is at its best when treated with the time it requires.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
